content:
Went with the fam over the weekend to “Shoshone Falls After Dark”. Here‘s a video sans loud DJ music. Definitely not near peak flow, but still gorgeous, and an awe-inspiring gift from our Creator. It always surprises me how few people know about this #Idaho gem that’s nicknamed “The Niagara of the West” (actually it’s taller).

If any of my #Native / #Indigenous cousins know what the Newenee call this waterfall, I would love for us all to learn.

{'id': '107709183005812841', 'username': 'shelenn', 'acct': 'shelenn@nerdica.net', 'display_name': 'Shelenn Ayres', 'locked': True, 'bot': False, 'discoverable': True, 'group': False, 'created_at': '2022-01-30T00:00:00.000Z', 'note': '

My name confuses some so let me tell you a bit about me. I\'ve been around 2.5D and 3D virtual worlds since their inception in the 90\'s after MUDs and MMOs. Yes Virginia, I remember 300 baud modems connected to the university VAX, working in octal on PDP8\'s, using BBS, exploring Windows 3.0, and of course ARPANET. It all began for me with the TI994A and a cassette recorder for a hard drive LOL until I graduated to BASIC-A and the PCJr while playing Tracer Sanction. 2.5D worlds still exist today but moving into Cybertown and Blaxxun along with Active Worlds brought me into 3D, I\'ve been there ever since.

Professionally, I am an Engineer with a well-rounded background who specializes in Modeling, Simulation, and Analysis. I am also into providing Research and Education services with a focus on Science, Technology, Engineering, and Math. However, I spend a lot of time working to advance technologies for Social 3D Virtual Worlds and Social VR applications with a focus on the user experience - especially when it comes to accessibility. Why? Because digitally marginalized users need someone in their corner! I am not talking about accommodation - I am talking about accessibility by design. Happy to have a conversation about this anytime!

While I\'ve been in most every 3D platform over the years, I am currently focused on supporting efforts to improve Open Simulator as a platform. Projects I am involved in run the gamut. How did I end up here? Some of my goals include integration with federated social media network type Friendica. I plan to integrate it with our R&D grid called Metaverse Depot connected to the Hypergrid as part of our mission to advance virtual world technologies with an organization I lead called Infinite Metaverse Alliance (IMA).

On the personal side, I won\'t list my favorite color, location, music genre, book, or movie. It\'s too difficult to choose! I consider myself a humanitarian who believes we are each other\'s keepers but I also believe the best offense is a strong defense - so some think that is just weird LOL. I view the greater community of virtual worlds encompasses online and offline space and that the virtual can be fantasy but it does not have to be. Offline I accept we are all flawed and we need some rules to protect us from ourselves. But that does not mean we should not push the boundaries for the sake of virtual evolution online! Social Virtual Worlds became a place I could be myself to create, build, script, share, and collaborate without traditional boundaries. It feels like home and I hope to extend that presence into the federated social web 😀

I will say the word Federation attracted me since I love Star Trek but my all-time favorite Science Fiction series is Babylon 5 as you may have guessed by my avatar name. My partner\'s name is Ivanova Ayres because she reminds me so much of that character. She dubbed me Shelenn as a cross between Sheridan and Delenn\'s characters (because she couldn\'t decide which I was most like) as we created accounts in Second Life when it began. The names stuck as we moved into the Open Simulator community ;)

#openSimulator #opensim #metaverseDepot #hypergrid #virtualWorlds #metaverse #socialVR #ugc #secondLife #SL #HG #nobot #noindex

"I\'d like you to take the time to learn the Babylon 5 mantra: \'Ivanova is always right. I will listen to Ivanova. I will not ignore Ivanova\'s recommendations. Ivanova is God. And if this ever happens again, Ivanova will personally rip your lungs out."
– Susan Ivanova

조선의 VoLTE가 세계표준과 사맛디 아니할세 야 이 통신3사 반란군노무 새끼들아.... (대충 탱크로 대갈통 날린다는 쌍욕)

구글 레퍼런스 포럼에서 나온 온갖종류의 트위킹을 해봐도 안됨.

그렇게 S10e를 3개월을 쓰다가 결국 중고로 S20fe를 샀다.
삼십만원 줬는데 사이드 한 군데 찍힌 상처 있고 배터리 수명이 10%정도 빠진 거 빼면 뭐.

어차피 폰 외관이야 케이스 끼우면 모르는 거고 배터리는 때되면 삼성서비스 가서 바꿔달라면 되니까.

그러고 나니 와 폰 새거 사서 못쓰겠더라....

content:
おとんの遺品のVHSはプロにデジタル化を任せようと思うが、おれが90～00年代に録画したVHS（画質が相当悪い）をどうしようと色々調べたら、IOデータとか、buffaloとかから出てる、PCとビデオデッキをちょちょっとつなげるキットを挟むだけで簡単にデジタル化できることがわかった。
そういうのがあるのは知ってたが、もっと面倒くさくて結構お値段すると思っていた。
今はUSBとケーブルさっさと挿すだけ。お値段も数千円で済む。お手頃なのをポチってさっそく古いビデオ鑑賞、もといデジタル化。
ユーティリティソフトが笑えるほど古臭いというか懐かしい感じｗ（Win11には対応してない）
PCディスプレイにビデオ録画した映像が映ったのには感動したｗ

São os "famosos quem?" da recó no novo reality que eu entendi bulhufas de como funciona a bagaça.
São desses que o público brasileiro gosta: pessoas que não tem medo e nem nada a perder, mesmo porque já perderam a dignidade há muito tempo pra aceitar o convite disso... Puro suco de um show de horror.

content: Unpopular Opinion: As a formally trained Fine Artist, I just can't get all orgasmic about AI-generated 'art'. Half of the sensual pleasure of art is working with various 3D mediums. But with this 2D digital imagery, that entire process is lost. Where are the creative decisions? Where is the unique mix of skill and emotional expression that connects the artist to the brush, the canvas, the observer? With AI we have none of that. Just a thoughtless rearrangement of images stolen from the web.
